mpute every future position exactly)\nGate A at (7,5): open exactly when (t mod 2) is in {1}. So it is open at t=1,3,... and closed at t=0,2,... You can only step ONTO it at a tick t+1 where it is open.\nGate B at (8,6): open exactly when (t mod 4) is in {0, 3}. So it is open at t=0,3,4,7,... and closed at t=1,2,5,6,... You can only step ONTO it at a tick t+1 where it is open.\nGuard P: walks a fixed cycle of length 4. Its position at tick t is determined by (t mod 4) as follows: t mod 4=0: (5,2); t mod 4=1: (6,2); t mod 4=2: (7,2); t mod 4=3: (6,2). This repeats forever.\nGuard Q: walks a fixed cycle of length 6. Its position at tick t is determined by (t mod 6) as follows: t mod 6=0: (2,8); t mod 6=1: (1,8); t mod 6=2: (1,7); t mod 6=3: (2,7); t mod 6=4: (1,7); t mod 6=5: (1,8). This repeats forever.\n\nYOUR JOB\nParcel 1: pick it up at (1,3) (map glyph '1'), deliver it to (5,8) (map glyph 'x'). Pickup and delivery happen automatically when you end a tick on the cell.\nParcel 2: pick it up at (2,1) (map glyph '2'), deliver it to (4,8) (map glyph 'y'). Pickup and delivery happen automatically when you end a tick on the cell.\nDeliver every parcel within 45 ticks. You move by committing to plans of\nexactly 5 moves at a time; you have at most 9 plans in total.\nIf you deliver the last parcel mid-plan, the game ends immediately and the unused\nmoves are discarded.\n\nWORKED EXAMPLE (for the rules only - this is NOT the map above): suppose you stand at\n(2,2), gate G at (3,2) has period 2 and is open when (t mod 2) = 1, and it is now t=0.\nMoving E now (arriving at t=1, when the gate is open) succeeds. But moving E at t=1\n(arriving at t=2, when the gate is closed) is a BUMP: you stay at (2,2) and tick 2 is\nwasted. The right play at t=1 is to WAIT once and then move E, arriving at t=3 when\nthe gate is open again.\n\nAfter each plan you receive only a per-tick log of OK/BUMP/CAUGHT/PICKED UP/DELIVERED. You are NEVER told where you are or why you bumped - track your p